Definition.WordDefinition: Stomp \Stomp\, v. i. [See {Stamp}.] To stamp with the foot. [Colloq.] ``In gallant procession, the priests mean to stomp.'' --R. Browning. [1913 Webster]
stomp n : a dance involving a rhythmical stamping step v : walk heavily; "The men stomped through the snow in their heavy boots" [syn: {stamp}, {stump}]
